docs.abstract: A federal judge found that President Trump’s former campaign chairman was untruthful about several topics, potentially leading to a longer sentence.
docs.snippet: A federal judge found that President Trump’s former campaign chairman was untruthful about several topics, potentially leading to a longer sentence.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A federal judge ruled on Wednesday that Paul Manafort, President Trump’s former campaign chairman, had breached his plea agreement by lying multiple times to prosecutors after pledging to cooperate with the special counsel’s investigation into Russia’s interference in the 2016 election.

headline.main: Manafort Lied After Plea Deal, Judge Says
headline.print_headline: Judge Supports Prosecutors’ View That Manafort Was Lying to Inquiry

docs.abstract: A procedural vote in the Senate shows that William P. Barr has enough support to be confirmed as head of the Justice Department later this week.
docs.snippet: A procedural vote in the Senate shows that William P. Barr has enough support to be confirmed as head of the Justice Department later this week.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — William P. Barr on Tuesday cleared a crucial hurdle for his nomination as attorney general, virtually assuring his confirmation this week to take over the Justice Department — and oversee the investigation into links between the Trump campaign and Russia’s election-manipulation operations.

headline.main: Barr Clears Key Hurdle for Confirmation as Attorney General
headline.print_headline: Attorney General Nominee Is Likely to Be Confirmed, Senate Vote Shows

docs.abstract: Retaining two counsels of Norman L. Eisen and Barry H. Berke’s caliber is relatively unusual for a congressional panel, and underscores the legal and political jeopardy the president faces.
docs.snippet: Retaining two counsels of Norman L. Eisen and Barry H. Berke’s caliber is relatively unusual for a congressional panel, and underscores the legal and political jeopardy the president faces.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Democrats on the House Judiciary Committee said on Tuesday that they had retained two elite white-collar litigators and prominent legal critics of President Trump to help begin inquiries into some of the most sensitive allegations involving the president, including ethics violations, corruption and possible obstruction of justice.

headline.main: House Judiciary Committee Hires Trump Legal Critics for Investigations
headline.print_headline: Trump Legal Critics Hired By House Judiciary Panel

docs.abstract: Congressional negotiators have come up with a tentative deal to avert a government shutdown. Here are some key takeaways.
docs.snippet: Congressional negotiators have come up with a tentative deal to avert a government shutdown. Here are some key takeaways.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The tentative deal reached late Monday by congressional negotiators to avert another government shutdown brought to the fore something President Trump has rarely seen in his time in office: reality-based programming.

headline.main: Five Key Takeaways From the Tentative Deal on Border Security

docs.abstract: House Republicans attached a resolution denouncing anti-Semitism to a Yemen war powers bill, trying to divide Democrats.
docs.snippet: House Republicans attached a resolution denouncing anti-Semitism to a Yemen war powers bill, trying to divide Democrats.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The House voted unanimously on Wednesday to condemn anti-Semitism and “all attempts to delegitimize and deny Israel’s right to exist,” adopting language put forth by Republicans who have spent weeks trying to paint two freshman Democrats as anti-Semites and dozens of other Democrats as their enablers.

headline.main: With Procedural Maneuver, House G.O.P. Elevates Anti-Semitism as Political Issue
headline.print_headline: House Backs G.O.P. Move Denouncing Anti-Semitism

docs.abstract: An executive order is the administration’s latest attempt to turn a provision from the sweeping 2017 tax law into a major effort to combat poverty.
docs.snippet: An executive order is the administration’s latest attempt to turn a provision from the sweeping 2017 tax law into a major effort to combat poverty.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump directed federal agencies on Wednesday to steer spending toward certain distressed communities across the country — part of his administration’s push to turn a tax break included in last year’s $1.5 trillion tax package into a broader effort to combat poverty and geographic inequality.

headline.main: Trump to Steer More Money to ‘Opportunity Zones’
headline.print_headline: President Makes Push To Increase Funding  For ‘Opportunity Zones’

docs.abstract: Ethics experts say Rudolph W. Giuliani risks blurring lines by seeking contracts with foreign governments even as he remains President Trump’s personal lawyer.
docs.snippet: Ethics experts say Rudolph W. Giuliani risks blurring lines by seeking contracts with foreign governments even as he remains President Trump’s personal lawyer.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The special counsel’s investigation was grinding relentlessly onward, with President Trump’s former national security adviser pleading for leniency in his case and his former fixer about to be sentenced for his crimes. But Mr. Trump’s personal lawyer, Rudolph W. Giuliani, was in Manama, Bahrain, on Tuesday, meeting with the king and the interior minister of an important United States ally in the Middle East.

headline.main: While Working for Trump, Giuliani Courts Business Abroad
headline.print_headline: Giuliani Chases Work Overseas, And Lines Blur

docs.abstract: The two parties typically try to avoid getting blamed for a government shutdown. President Trump says he’s happy to own one over a border wall.
docs.snippet: The two parties typically try to avoid getting blamed for a government shutdown. President Trump says he’s happy to own one over a border wall.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The trick in Washington has always been to make sure a government shutdown is pinned on the other guy. President Trump is the first to ever pin one on himself.

headline.main: Playing by His Own Rules, Trump Flips the Shutdown Script
headline.print_headline: Embracing Blame, Trump Flips the Shutdown Script

docs.abstract: The meeting, to be held in Washington this month between midlevel officials, comes as the Trump administration is preparing more tariffs on Chinese goods.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The United States and China will return to the negotiating table late this month in an attempt to ease months of tensions that have been building since trade talks broke down this year and both countries began imposing escalating rounds of tariffs on each other.

docs.abstract: After last year’s harsh lessons, the administration girded for a test of its ability as Hurricane Florence approached the Carolina coast.
docs.snippet: After last year’s harsh lessons, the administration girded for a test of its ability as Hurricane Florence approached the Carolina coast.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A year after presiding over a sluggish and chaotic response to a devastating storm in Puerto Rico, the Trump administration girded on Wednesday for a test of its ability to do better as Hurricane Florence continued to bear down on the Carolina coast.

headline.main: Hurricane Florence Is a Formidable Test for FEMA and Trump
headline.print_headline: Storm Presents Test for FEMA And President

byline.original: By Ron Nixon, Julie Hirschfeld Davis and James Glanz
